  "body": "* **I'm submitting a ...**\r\n\r\n  * \\[ ] Feature request\r\n  * \\[X] Bug report\r\n\r\n* **Bug Report**\r\n  * What is the current behavior?\r\n\r\nI generated an ERC20 token transaction using MEW send offline tool.  I entered the following amount to transfer:\r\n\r\n1213.910141883648668948\r\n\r\nThe generated transaction contained the following rounded amount instead:\r\n\r\n1213910141883650000000\r\n\r\nNo warning was given that this occurred, and since it was the entire balance, the transaction used up the entire gas limit and then failed with an error.\r\n\r\n  * If the current behavior is a bug, please provide the steps to reproduce and if possible a minimal demo of the problem\r\n\r\nSee above.\r\n\r\n  * What is the expected behavior?\r\n\r\nNo rounding, or if rounding is technically required for some reason, a warning when it occurs, and a reminder to verify that the balance is sufficient.\r\n\r\n  * What is the motivation / use case for changing the behavior?\r\n\r\nThis cost me $5 in fees!\r\n\r\n  * Please tell us about your environment:\r\n    * Operating system\r\n    * Browser and version\r\n\r\nFirefox 61.0.1 on Ubuntu 18.04 (offline machine)\r\n\r\n  * Other information (e.g. detailed explanation, stacktraces, related issues, suggestions how to fix, links for us to have context, eg. stackoverflow, gitter, etc)\r\n  * Where can this be found? e.g: `/interface`, `/create-wallet`, etc.\r\n\r\n/interface/send-offline",
